0raising%20a%20child%20in%20China%20is%20no%20small%20feat%2C%20costing%20an%20average%20of%20%2474%2C800%20until%20age%2017%2C%20and%20a%20staggering%20%2494%2C500%20for%20a%20full%20bachelor's%20degree.%20This%20financial%20burden%20is%20particularly%20heavy%2C%20as%20it's%206.3%20times%20higher%20than%20China's%20GDP%20per%20capita%2C%20surpassing%20all%20but%20South%20Korea's%20eye-watering%207.79%20times%20ratio.%20The%20report%20highlights%20a%20stark%20contrast%20with%20other%20developed%20nations%2C%20with%20child-rearing%20costs%20only%202-4%20times%20the%20GDP%20per%20capita%20in%20Australia%2C%20France%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20Japan.%20These%20findings%20raise%20concerns%20about%20the%20impact%20on%20fertility%20rates%20in%20China%2C%20which%20is%20already%20facing%20a%20demographic%20decline%20and%20an%20aging%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20led%20by%20Liang%20Jianzhang%2C%20a%20notable%20entrepreneur%20and%20economics%20professor%20at%20Peking%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20report%20from%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2Ffeb%2F21%2Fcost-of-raising-children-in-china-is-second-highest-in-the-world-think-tank-reveals%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20Guardian%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20China's%20population%20declined%20for%20the%20second%20consecutive%20year%20last%20year%2C%20raising%20concerns%20for%20the%20government%20as%20it%20faces%20challenges%20in%20supporting%20an%20aging%20population%20with%20a%20diminishing%20workforce.%20The%20number%20of%20births%20in%202023%20was%20slightly%20over%209%20million%2C%20which%20is%20approximately%20half%20of%20the%202016%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20women%20are%20opting%20to%20delay%20or%20forgo%20motherhood%20due%20to%20concerns%20about%20its%20negative%20impact%20on%20their%20careers%20and%20finances.%20In%202017%2C%20the%20government%20abandoned%20the%20long-standing%20one-child%20policy%20and%20now%20encourages%20women%20to%20have%20up%