time...%20while%20at%20the%20undersigned%20counsel's%20law%20office%20for%20meetings%20with%20counsel%2C%26quot%3B%20his%20lawyers%20David%20Chesnoff%20and%20Richard%20Schonfeld%20said%20in%20a%20court%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20should%20further%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Defendant%20was%20attending%20a%20legal%20consultation%20meeting%20at%20his%20attorneys'%20office%20contradicts%20the%20notion%20that%20he%20is%20a%20risk%20of%20flight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20motion%2C%20filed%20in%20Clark%20County%2C%20Nevada%2C%20seeks%20an%20immediate%20hearing%20to%20order%20Smirnov's%20release%20from%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20grand%20jury%20indictment%20against%20Smirnov%20that%20was%20unsealed%20last%20week%20appears%20to%20undermine%20the%20impeachment%20effort%20against%20Biden%20being%20put%20together%20by%20congressional%20Republicans%2C%20who%20had%20touted%20Smirnov's%20evidence%20as%20proof%20the%20Bidens%20were%20collectively%20involved%20in%20a%20criminal%20enterprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%20that%20Hunter%20Biden%20leveraged%20his%20father's%20name%20for%20personal%20gain%20has%20been%20central%20to%20a%20Republican%20narrative%2C%20pushed%20heavily%20by%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20that%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20corrupt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20said%20that%20for%20at%20least%20a%20decade%20Smirnov%20was%20acting%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bconfidential%20human%20source%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20Federal%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%2C%20providing%20his%20handler%20with%20information%20to%20be%20used%20in%20criminal%20investigations%2C%20and%20that%20some%20of%20what%20he%20passed%20on%20was%20false.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20subsequent%20filing%20claimed%20that%20Russia's%20intelligence%20services%20were%20the%20root%20of%20the%20false%20information%20Smirnov%20had%20given%20to%20his%20FBI%20handler%20about%20the%20Bidens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20the%20efforts%20were%20not%20onl