%20a%20form%20of%20cognitive%20decline%20that%20can%20cause%20memory%20loss%20and%20personality%20changes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETalk%20show%20host%20Wendy%20Williams%20and%20actor%20Bruce%20Willis%20have%20both%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20the%20condition.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20can%20occur%20at%20a%20younger%20age%20than%20Alzheimer's%2C%20typically%20in%20people%20aged%2040%20to%2060%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBroadcast%20media%20star%20Wendy%20Williams%20has%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20frontotemporal%20dementia%20and%20primary%20progressive%20aphasia%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prnewswire.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fwendy-williams-diagnosed-with-primary-progressive-aphasia-and-dementia-302068851.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20her%20care%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20related%20neurodegenerative%20conditions%20can%20both%20cause%20issues%20with%20memory%20and%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams'%20diagnosis%20was%20announced%20February%2022.%20The%20former%20talk%20show%20host%20had%20previously%20stepped%20down%20from%20her%20namesake%20show%20after%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwendy-williams-has-serious-health-complications-wont-return-to-show-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bserious%20complications%26quot%3B%20of%20other%20health%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Foveractive-thyroid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGraves'%20Disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20Williams%20had%20begun%20to%20show%20signs%20of%20erratic%20behavior%2C%20confusion%2C%20and%20loss%20of%20words%2C%20according%20to%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20many%20individuals%20diagnosed%20with%20aphasia%20and%20frontotemporal%20dementia%20face%20stigma%20and%20misunderstanding%2C%20particularly%20when%20they%20begin%20to%20exhibit%20behavioral%20changes%20but%20have%20not%20yet%20received%20a%20diagnosis%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20condition%20has%20received%20more%20public%20awareness%20due%20to%20other%20high-profile%20cases%20in%20celebrities%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbruce-willis-diagnosis-frontotemporal-dementia-symptoms-treatment-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBruce%20Willis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20family%20announced%20his%20diagnosis%20in%20February%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20currently%20no%20cure%20or%20treatment%20for%20the%20condition%2C%20and%20it%20is%20known%20to%20progress%20over%20time%2C%20causing%20further%20decline%20in%20patients'%20ability%20to%20make%20decisions%20and%20communicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20of%20frontotemporal%20dementia%3A%20difficulty%20communicating%2C%20changes%20to%20mood%20and%20behavior%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrontotemporal%20dementia%20refers%20to%20a%20group%20of%20disorders%20caused%20by%20nerve%20cell%20damage%20to%20areas%20of%20the%20brain%20behind%20the%20forehead%20(in%20the%20frontal%20lobe)%20and%20behind%20the%20ears%20(in%20the%20temporal%20lobes).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20parts%20of%20the%20brain%20help%20control%20language%20and%20behavior%2C%20so%20people%20with%20the%20condition%20can%20experience%20symptoms%20such%20as%20difficulty%20communicating%2C%20impulsive%20actions%2C%20or%20major%20personality%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Fdiseases-conditions%2Fprimary-progressive-aphasia%2Fsymptoms-causes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrimary%20progressive%20aphasia%20falls%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20FTD.%3C%2Fa%3E%20It%20is%20a%20condition%20that%20affects%20a%20person's%20ability%20to%20communicate.%20Symptoms%20begin%20slowly%20and%20gradually%2C%20but%20over%20time%20can%20cause%20people%20to%20lose%20the%20ability%20to%20speak%2C%20write%2C%20or%20understand%20language%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrontotemporal%20dementia%20can%20also%20have%20symptoms%20such%20as%20memory%20loss%2C%20but%20unlike%20other%20forms%20of%20dementia%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falzheimers-and-dementia-misconceptions-and-surprising-facts-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlzheimer's%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20typically%20occurs%20in%20younger%20people.%20Most%20cases%20of%20frontotemporal%20dementia%20are%20in%20people%20aged%2045%20to%2064%2C%20and%20it%20is%20the%20most%20common%20form%20of%20cognitive%20decline%20in%20people%20under%2060%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaftd.org%2Fwhat-is-ftd%2Fdisease-overview%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAssociation%20for%20Frontotemporal%20Degeneration%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-frontotemporal-dementia-ftd-symptoms-causes-treatment%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708651171000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d7bb8d90413ab8e1d636f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-frontotemporal-dementia-ftd-symptoms-causes-treatment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Frontotemporal%20dementia%20and%20a%20related%20condition%20called%20aphasia%20have%20symptoms%20such%20as%20difficulty%20communicating%2C%20loss%20of%20words%2C%20and%20erratic%20behavior.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-frontotemporal-dementia-ftd-symptoms-causes-treatment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B