20Washington%20State%20district%20court.%20Business%20Insider%20reviewed%20both%20complaints%2C%20one%20of%20which%20was%20filed%20on%20behalf%20of%20plaintiff%20Mariana%20Franzetti%20on%20February%2012%20and%20the%20other%20on%20behalf%20of%20Robin%20Krohn%20on%20February%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consumers%20said%20PMI%20withheld%20information%20that%20would%20have%20impacted%20their%20decisions%20to%20buy%20Stanley%20products%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20Specifically%2C%20the%20complaints%20say%20the%20company%20should%20have%20advertised%20to%20customers%20that%20its%20cups%20contain%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstanley-tumblers-lead-owala-hydro-flask-seize-moment-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanley%20has%20previously%20stated%20its%20cups%20are%20safe%20for%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fmoney%2F2024%2F02%2F20%2Fstanley-cup-lead-lawsuits%2F72672442007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSA%20Today%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20it%20would%20%26quot%3Bvigorously%20defend%20itself%20against%20meritless%20claims%2C%26quot%3B%20reiterating%20that%20the%20surface%20of%20its%20product%20contains%20no%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPMI%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20say%20Stanley's%20parent%20company%20withheld%20information%20from%20consumers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFranzetti%2C%20who%20purchased%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-stanley-cup-wedding-day-harry-potter-books-quencher-collection-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanley%20cup%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%2435%20in%20March%202023%2C%20said%20in%20her%20complaint%20that%20it%20was%20now%20%26quot%3Bessentially%20worthless%26quot%3B%20to%20her%20because%20it%20contained%20%26quot%3Blead%2